messages.message: I’ve been having trouble locally with my different services communicating, anyone else see this issue? For instance, it would take minutes for app-tasks to send some request to webdriver-tasks, and restarting rabbit mq would push it through

I’ve been getting errors like this

```[2019-11-13 19:32:59,452: ERROR/ForkPoolWorker-4] Read empty data, calling disconnect
[2019-11-13 19:32:59,453: INFO/ForkPoolWorker-4] Disconnected from RabbitMQ at 127.0.0.1:5672 (-1): EOF
[2019-11-13 19:32:59,455: ERROR/ForkPoolWorker-4] Connection close detected; result=BlockingConnection__OnClosedArgs(connection=<SelectConnection CLOSED socket=None params=<ConnectionParameters host=127.0.0.1 port=5672 virtual_host=/ ssl=False>>, reason_code=-1, reason_text='EOF')
[2019-11-13 19:32:59,456: INFO/ForkPoolWorker-4] --- Attempting connection with RabbitMQ ---
[2019-11-13 19:32:59,457: INFO/ForkPoolWorker-4] Connecting to 127.0.0.1:5672
[2019-11-13 19:32:59,465: INFO/ForkPoolWorker-4] Created channel=1
[2019-11-13 19:32:59,471: ERROR/ForkPoolWorker-4] Could not export entity [55b21551-21f8-44fc-ab55-e7e522982a65] to endpoint```
Not sure if it’s related — doesn’t slow down performance too much, but seems to be some kind of problem with rabbitmq
That is actually OK.  Our export libraries reconnect with rabbitmq once the connection becomes stale or dormant
I figured it out… apparently I had two instances of webdriver-tasks and app-tasks running lol
